cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NA 

This paper deals with signal and image processing, specifically sparse representation methodology and variational strategy. The paper proposes a new sparsity-based model for solving overparameterized variational problems, which can be used for denoising and segmentation of images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of sparse representation methodology and variational strategy also falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which can be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
